<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-624-870  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 624 870.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 25 1990 v4 n25 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD chops ADP, pushes joint command. (a Department of Defensereport recommends overhall of DOD)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob; Marsan, Carolyn Duffy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A 'closely-held, limited-circulation' Department of Defense (DOD)report by the office of DOD Deputy Comptroller Cynthia Kendallproposes a drastic overhaul of DOD automatic data processing (ADP)management and acquisition by the establishment of command withinan existing DOD agency to consolidate the 'administrative ADPcenters' and 46 'central design activities' of the three servicesand the Defense Logistics Agency (DLA).andP;  Consolidation of 2,000DLA and military services data processing centers into 18 'magnetprocessing centers' is urged.andP;  Military and industry observersexpect the services to fight the plan.andP;  The Defense CommunicationsAgency is the most likely agency to run the new command.andO;Observers believe the consolidation is possible, but thetransition will be difficult, with much hardware and software toreplace, update and integrate.andP;  Defense contractors will benefitby the consolidation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ReorganizationData ProcessingMilitaryIntegrated ApproachGoals and ObjectivesPlanningUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>